bug.short_desc: put files required for managing Trac, Bugzilla, Hudson, Jenkins and Gerrit instances under version control

long_desc.thetext: We have a number of scripts and configuration files that we use to provision and manage test server instances. These should be under version control in Git along with the the sources.
Frank, I'll take a first pass at this.

I have pushed a first pass for Hudson/Jenkins into org.eclipse.mylyn.builds/org.eclipse.mylyn.hudson.releng/. We'll need to do the same for the other repositories so we can provision them including all sample data fully automatically add new versions easily.

I added an initial version for a vagrant/puppet configuration to provision a VM with several versions of Hudson and Jenkins. To run it simply execute vagrant.sh in org.eclipse.mylyn.releng/vagrant. The web server in the VM is mapped to port 8080. Hudson 2.2 is accessible from http://localhost:8080/hudson-2.2 for instance once the VM is up.

I added a module for trac that automatically provisions 9 trac instances with different versions and authentication methods.
Frank, we'll need to do something similar for Bugzilla. If you are interested you can try it by running "vagrant up" in the org.eclipse.mylyn/org.eclipse.mylyn.releng/vagrant directory. You'll need to have vagrant installed (http://vagrantup.com/).
Once the VM is provisioned and running you can access the trac instances at http://localhost:2080/trac-0.12.
To access the shell on the VM use "vagrant ssh" and to shutdown the VM just run "vagrant halt". You can get rid of the VM by running "vagrant destroy".

with the following an an replacement of /org.eclipse.mylyn.releng/vagrant/Vagrantfile Vagrant::Config.run do |config| config.vm.define :trac do |trac_config| trac_config.vm.box = "lucid32" trac_config.vm.box_url = "http://files.vagrantup.com/lucid32.box"
trac_config.vm.provision :puppet do |puppet| puppet.module_path = "../../../org.eclipse.mylyn.tasks/org.eclipse.mylyn.trac.releng/modules" puppet.manifests_path = "../../../org.eclipse.mylyn.tasks/org.eclipse.mylyn.trac.releng/modules/trac/manifests" puppet.manifest_file = "trac.pp" end trac_config.vm.provision :shell, :path => "../../../org.eclipse.mylyn.tasks/org.eclipse.mylyn.trac.releng/scripts/start.sh" trac_config.vm.forward_port 80, 3080 trac_config.vm.forward_port 443, 3443 end
config.vm.define :bugzilla do |bugzilla_config| bugzilla_config.vm.box = "lucid32" bugzilla_config.vm.box_url = "http://files.vagrantup.com/lucid32.box"
bugzilla_config.vm.provision :puppet do |puppet| puppet.module_path = "../../../org.eclipse.mylyn.tasks/org.eclipse.mylyn.bugzilla.releng/modules" puppet.manifests_path = "../../../org.eclipse.mylyn.tasks/org.eclipse.mylyn.bugzilla.releng/modules/bugzilla/manifests" puppet.manifest_file = "bugzilla.pp" end bugzilla_config.vm.forward_port 80, 3081 bugzilla_config.vm.forward_port 443, 3444 end end

we now have the following reviews: * The Vagrant files for Bugzilla https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/8033/ * The Bugzilla test changes https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/8489/ * The changes for Trac https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/8488/
I noticed that we still use lucid (10.04) as the base for the VMs. We should consider switching to precise (12.04) which is the latest LTS.

I modified a few things in the last patch set: * The mysql root password is not changed. This would interfere with other puppet scripts running on the same VM. * All perl modules are consumed as system packages to avoid long perl compile processes. * XML-RPC is disabled by modifying the script rather than relying on a perl module not being present. * The Vagrant port is changes to be consistent with other Mylyn configurations.
Frank, I would prefer if the Bugzilla Apache configurations were located under /home/tools/bugzilla rather than in the global configuration and included in the same way as the Trac sites.

I have pushed a review for the global VM configuration here: https://git.eclipse.org/r/8528. It doesn't work as expected though. Only the Gerrit provisioner runs. We probably need to set that up differently.

Puppet provisioning is now invoked through the shell which allows us to invoke puppet several times with different configurations. I have opened a few more tasks to track the remaining work: bug 394051, bug 394052, bug 394053.

Puppet based provisioning now works for all supported repository types: Bugzilla, Gerrit, Hudson, Jenkins, Trac. It's as easy as typing "vagrant up" to provision the a full local Mylyn test environment in a VM.
The test repositories on mylyn.org are provisioned using the same puppet based infrastructure. Repositories are currently updated manually when the puppet configuration changes but work is underway to fully automate the process (bug 394052).
